{
  "_id": "titus",
  "title": "Titus",
  "subtitle": "",
  "delineation": "Chapter",
  "chapters": [
    {
      "number": 1,
      "verses": [
        {
          "text": "Paul, a servant of God, and an apostle of Jesus Christ, according to the faith of God's elect, and the acknowledging of the truth which is after godliness;",
          "footnotes": [
            {
              "footnote": "TG Servant.",
              "start": 8,
              "end": 15
            },
            {
              "footnote": "TG Apostles.",
              "start": 31,
              "end": 38
            },
            {
              "footnote": "TG Election.",
              "start": 88,
              "end": 93
            }
          ],
          "associatedContents": [],
          "italics": []
        },
        {
          "text": "In hope of eternal life, which God, that cannot lie, promised before the world began;",
          "footnotes": [
            {
              "footnote": "TG Hope.",
              "start": 3,
              "end": 7
            },
            {
              "footnote": "TG Salvation, Plan of.",
              "start": 11,
              "end": 23
            },
            {
              "footnote": "TG God, Perfection of; Lying.",
              "start": 48,
              "end": 51
            },
            {
              "footnote": "2 Tim. 1:1; Abr. 3:26.",
              "start": 53,
              "end": 61
            }
          ],
          "associatedContents": [],
          "italics": []
        },
        {
          "text": "But hath in due times manifested his word through preaching, which is committed unto me according to the commandment of God our Saviour;",
          "footnotes": [],
          "associatedContents": [],
          "italics": []
        },
        {
          "text": "To Titus, mine own son after the common faith: Grace, mercy, and peace, from God the Father and the Lord Jesus Christ our Saviour.",
          "footnotes": [],
          "associatedContents": [],
          "italics": [
            {
              "start": 10,
              "end": 14
            },
            {
              "start": 61,
              "end": 64
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "text": "For this cause left I thee in Crete, that thou shouldest set in order the things that are wanting, and ordain elders in every city, as I had appointed thee:",
          "footnotes": [
            {
              "footnote": "TG Order.",
              "start": 64,
              "end": 69
            },
            {
              "footnote": "TG Priesthood, Authority; Priesthood, Ordination.",
              "start": 103,
              "end": 109
            },
            {
              "footnote": "TG Church Organization; Elder, Melchizedek Priesthood.",
              "start": 110,
              "end": 116
            },
            {
              "footnote": "GR directed, ordered.",
              "start": 141,
              "end": 150
            }
          ],
          "associatedContents": [],
          "italics": []
        },
        {
          "text": "If any be blameless, the husband of one wife, having faithful children not accused of riot or unruly.",
          "footnotes": [
            {
              "footnote": "GR debauchery or insubordination.",
              "start": 86,
              "end": 100
            }
          ],
          "associatedContents": [],
          "italics": []
        },
        {
          "text": "For a bishop must be blameless, as the steward of God; not selfwilled, not soon angry, not given to wine, no striker, not given to filthy lucre;",
          "footnotes": [
            {
              "footnote": "TG Bishop; Leadership.",
              "start": 6,
              "end": 12
            },
            {
              "footnote": "TG Delegation of Responsibility; Stewardship.",
              "start": 39,
              "end": 46
            },
            {
              "footnote": "GR obstinate, arrogant.",
              "start": 59,
              "end": 69
            },
            {
              "footnote": "TG Anger.",
              "start": 80,
              "end": 85
            }
          ],
          "associatedContents": [],
          "italics": []
        },
        {
          "text": "But a lover of hospitality, a lover of good men, sober, just, holy, temperate;",
          "footnotes": [
            {
              "footnote": "TG Hospitality.",
              "start": 15,
              "end": 26
            },
            {
              "footnote": "GR what is good.",
              "start": 39,
              "end": 47
            },
            {
              "footnote": "GR self-controlled. TG Temperance.",
              "start": 68,
              "end": 77
            }
          ],
          "associatedContents": [],
          "italics": []
        },
        {
          "text": "Holding fast the faithful word as he hath been taught, that he may be able by sound doctrine both to exhort and to convince the gainsayers.",
          "footnotes": [
            {
              "footnote": "D&C 11:21.",
              "start": 115,
              "end": 123
            },
            {
              "footnote": "GR those who deny, contradict.",
              "start": 128,
              "end": 138
            }
          ],
          "associatedContents": [],
          "italics": []
        },
        {
          "text": "For there are many unruly and vain talkers and deceivers, specially they of the circumcision:",
          "footnotes": [
            {
              "footnote": "GR idle speakers, disputers.",
              "start": 30,
              "end": 42
            },
            {
              "footnote": "TG Apostasy of the Early Christian Church.",
              "start": 47,
              "end": 56
            },
            {
              "footnote": "TG Circumcision.",
              "start": 80,
              "end": 92
            }
          ],
          "associatedContents": [],
          "italics": []
        },
        {
          "text": "Whose mouths must be stopped, who subvert whole houses, teaching things which they ought not, for filthy lucre's sake.",
          "footnotes": [
            {
              "footnote": "1 Tim. 6:5; Mosiah 29:40; Alma 11:24.",
              "start": 105,
              "end": 112
            }
          ],
          "associatedContents": [
            {
              "type": "paper-page-number",
              "data": 1518
            }
          ],
          "italics": []
        },
        {
          "text": "One of themselves, even a prophet of their own, said, The Cretians are alway liars, evil beasts, slow bellies.",
          "footnotes": [
            {
              "footnote": "GR lazy gluttons.",
              "start": 97,
              "end": 109
            }
          ],
          "associatedContents": [],
          "italics": [
            {
              "start": 19,
              "end": 23
            },
            {
              "start": 67,
              "end": 70
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "text": "This witness is true. Wherefore rebuke them sharply, that they may be sound in the faith;",
          "footnotes": [
            {
              "footnote": "D&C 84:117 (87, 117).",
              "start": 32,
              "end": 38
            }
          ],
          "associatedContents": [],
          "italics": []
        },
        {
          "text": "Not giving heed to Jewish fables, and commandments of men, that turn from the truth.",
          "footnotes": [
            {
              "footnote": "1 Tim. 1:4.",
              "start": 26,
              "end": 32
            },
            {
              "footnote": "Matt. 15:9; Col. 2:22; D&C 3:6 (6–7); 45:29; 46:7; JS—H 1:19.",
              "start": 38,
              "end": 50
            },
            {
              "footnote": "GR who reject, repudiate the truth.",
              "start": 59,
              "end": 63
            }
          ],
          "associatedContents": [],
          "italics": []
        },
        {
          "text": "Unto the pure all things are pure: but unto them that are defiled and unbelieving is nothing pure; but even their mind and conscience is defiled.",
          "footnotes": [
            {
              "footnote": "JST Titus 1:15 Unto the pure, let all things be pure …",
              "start": 0,
              "end": 4
            },
            {
              "footnote": "TG Purity.",
              "start": 29,
              "end": 33
            },
            {
              "footnote": "TG Pollution.",
              "start": 58,
              "end": 65
            },
            {
              "footnote": "Luke 11:39 (39–41). TG Mind.",
              "start": 114,
              "end": 118
            },
            {
              "footnote": "TG Conscience.",
              "start": 123,
              "end": 133
            },
            {
              "footnote": "Mark 7:15; 2 Ne. 19:17; D&C 93:35.",
              "start": 137,
              "end": 144
            }
          ],
          "associatedContents": [],
          "italics": [
            {
              "start": 25,
              "end": 28
            },
            {
              "start": 82,
              "end": 84
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "text": "They profess that they know God; but in works they deny him, being abominable, and disobedient, and unto every good work reprobate.",
          "footnotes": [
            {
              "footnote": "Matt. 7:21 (21–23). TG False Prophets; Hypocrisy.",
              "start": 5,
              "end": 12
            },
            {
              "footnote": "Hosea 8:2. TG Ignorance.",
              "start": 23,
              "end": 27
            },
            {
              "footnote": "Matt. 15:8 (7–9).",
              "start": 40,
              "end": 45
            },
            {
              "footnote": "TG Apostasy of the Early Christian Church.",
              "start": 51,
              "end": 55
            },
            {
              "footnote": "TG Disobedience.",
              "start": 83,
              "end": 94
            },
            {
              "footnote": "GR unfit, worthless.",
              "start": 121,
              "end": 130
            }
          ],
          "associatedContents": [],
          "italics": [
            {
              "start": 56,
              "end": 60
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "number": 2,
      "verses": [
        {
          "text": "But speak thou the things which become sound doctrine:",
          "footnotes": [
            {
              "footnote": "1 Thes. 2:4; 1 Pet. 4:11. TG Teaching.",
              "start": 4,
              "end": 9
            },
            {
              "footnote": "D&C 88:77 (77–78).",
              "start": 45,
              "end": 53
            }
          ],
          "associatedContents": [],
          "italics": []
        },
        {
          "text": "That the aged men be sober, grave, temperate, sound in faith, in charity, in patience.",
          "footnotes": [
            {
              "footnote": "TG Old Age.",
              "start": 9,
              "end": 13
            },
            {
              "footnote": "GR circumspect.",
              "start": 21,
              "end": 26
            },
            {
              "footnote": "TG Temperance.",
              "start": 35,
              "end": 44
            }
          ],
          "associatedContents": [],
          "italics": []
        },
        {
          "text": "The aged women likewise, that they be in behaviour as becometh holiness, not false accusers, not given to much wine, teachers of good things;",
          "footnotes": [
            {
              "footnote": "GR slanderers, traitors, devils.",
              "start": 77,
              "end": 82
            },
            {
              "footnote": "TG Gossip.",
              "start": 83,
              "end": 91
            }
          ],
          "associatedContents": [],
          "italics": [
            {
              "start": 30,
              "end": 37
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "text": "That they may teach the young women to be sober, to love their husbands, to love their children,",
          "footnotes": [
            {
              "footnote": "TG Marriage, Wives.",
              "start": 30,
              "end": 35
            },
            {
              "footnote": "TG Family, Love within.",
              "start": 52,
              "end": 56
            }
          ],
          "associatedContents": [],
          "italics": []
        },
        {
          "text": "To be discreet, chaste, keepers at home, good, obedient to their own husbands, that the word of God be not blasphemed.",
          "footnotes": [
            {
              "footnote": "TG Chastity; Modesty.",
              "start": 16,
              "end": 22
            },
            {
              "footnote": "GR housekeepers, guards.",
              "start": 24,
              "end": 31
            },
            {
              "footnote": "1 Tim. 5:14.",
              "start": 35,
              "end": 39
            }
          ],
          "associatedContents": [],
          "italics": [
            {
              "start": 0,
              "end": 5
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "text": "Young men likewise exhort to be sober minded.",
          "footnotes": [],
          "associatedContents": [],
          "italics": []
        },
        {
          "text": "In all things shewing thyself a pattern of good works: in doctrine shewing uncorruptness, gravity, sincerity,",
          "footnotes": [
            {
              "footnote": "GR dignity, respectfulness.",
              "start": 90,
              "end": 97
            },
            {
              "footnote": "TG Sincere.",
              "start": 99,
              "end": 108
            }
          ],
          "associatedContents": [],
          "italics": [
            {
              "start": 67,
              "end": 74
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "text": "Sound speech, that cannot be condemned; that he that is of the contrary part may be ashamed, having no evil thing to say of you.",
          "footnotes": [
            {
              "footnote": "1 Tim. 6:3.",
              "start": 0,
              "end": 5
            },
            {
              "footnote": "1 Pet. 2:12 (11–12).",
              "start": 29,
              "end": 38
            },
            {
              "footnote": "GR an opponent, enemy.",
              "start": 56,
              "end": 76
            }
          ],
          "associatedContents": [],
          "italics": []
        },
        {
          "text": "Exhort servants to be obedient unto their own masters, and to please them well in all things; not answering again;",
          "footnotes": [
            {
              "footnote": "Eph. 6:5; Col. 3:22; 1 Tim. 6:1 (1–2); 1 Pet. 2:18.",
              "start": 7,
              "end": 15
            },
            {
              "footnote": "GR arguing against, opposing, contradicting.",
              "start": 98,
              "end": 113
            }
          ],
          "associatedContents": [],
          "italics": [
            {
              "start": 0,
              "end": 6
            },
            {
              "start": 55,
              "end": 58
            },
            {
              "start": 69,
              "end": 73
            },
            {
              "start": 86,
              "end": 93
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "text": "Not purloining, but shewing all good fidelity; that they may adorn the doctrine of God our Saviour in all things.",
          "footnotes": [
            {
              "footnote": "GR misappropriating, robbing. TG Stealing.",
              "start": 4,
              "end": 14
            },
            {
              "footnote": "GR honor, put in order.",
              "start": 61,
              "end": 66
            }
          ],
          "associatedContents": [],
          "italics": []
        },
        {
          "text": "For the grace of God that bringeth salvation hath appeared to all men,",
          "footnotes": [
            {
              "footnote": "TG Grace.",
              "start": 8,
              "end": 13
            },
            {
              "footnote": "JST Titus 2:11 … which bringeth salvation to all men, hath appeared;",
              "start": 21,
              "end": 25
            }
          ],
          "associatedContents": [],
          "italics": []
        },
        {
          "text": "Teaching us that, denying ungodliness and worldly lusts, we should live soberly, righteously, and godly, in this present world;",
          "footnotes": [
            {
              "footnote": "TG Godliness.",
              "start": 26,
              "end": 37
            },
            {
              "footnote": "TG Worldliness.",
              "start": 42,
              "end": 49
            },
            {
              "footnote": "TG Lust.",
              "start": 50,
              "end": 55
            },
            {
              "footnote": "TG Levity.",
              "start": 72,
              "end": 79
            },
            {
              "footnote": "TG Abundant Life; Righteousness.",
              "start": 81,
              "end": 92
            }
          ],
          "associatedContents": [],
          "italics": []
        },
        {
          "text": "Looking for that blessed hope, and the glorious appearing of the great God and our Saviour Jesus Christ;",
          "footnotes": [
            {
              "footnote": "TG Glory.",
              "start": 39,
              "end": 47
            }
          ],
          "associatedContents": [],
          "italics": []
        },
        {
          "text": "Who gave himself for us, that he might redeem us from all iniquity, and purify unto himself a peculiar people, zealous of good works.",
          "footnotes": [
            {
              "footnote": "TG Self-Sacrifice.",
              "start": 9,
              "end": 16
            },
            {
              "footnote": "TG Jesus Christ, Atonement through; Jesus Christ, Redeemer; Redemption.",
              "start": 39,
              "end": 45
            },
            {
              "footnote": "TG Purification; Purity.",
              "start": 72,
              "end": 78
            },
            {
              "footnote": "TG Peculiar People.",
              "start": 94,
              "end": 109
            },
            {
              "footnote": "TG Zeal.",
              "start": 111,
              "end": 118
            }
          ],
          "associatedContents": [],
          "italics": []
        },
        {
          "text": "These things speak, and exhort, and rebuke with all authority. Let no man despise thee.",
          "footnotes": [
            {
              "footnote": "TG Chastening.",
              "start": 36,
              "end": 42
            },
            {
              "footnote": "TG Authority.",
              "start": 52,
              "end": 61
            },
            {
              "footnote": "GR disregard.",
              "start": 74,
              "end": 81
            }
          ],
          "associatedContents": [],
          "italics": []
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "number": 3,
      "verses": [
        {
          "text": "Put them in mind to be subject to principalities and powers, to obey magistrates, to be ready to every good work,",
          "footnotes": [
            {
              "footnote": "TG Citizenship.",
              "start": 23,
              "end": 30
            },
            {
              "footnote": "TG Governments.",
              "start": 34,
              "end": 48
            }
          ],
          "associatedContents": [],
          "italics": []
        },
        {
          "text": "To speak evil of no man, to be no brawlers, but gentle, shewing all meekness unto all men.",
          "footnotes": [
            {
              "footnote": "TG Slander.",
              "start": 3,
              "end": 13
            },
            {
              "footnote": "GR not quarrelsome.",
              "start": 31,
              "end": 42
            },
            {
              "footnote": "D&C 38:41.",
              "start": 68,
              "end": 76
            }
          ],
          "associatedContents": [],
          "italics": [
            {
              "start": 44,
              "end": 47
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "text": "For we ourselves also were sometimes foolish, disobedient, deceived, serving divers lusts and pleasures, living in malice and envy, hateful, and hating one another.",
          "footnotes": [
            {
              "footnote": "GR once, formerly.",
              "start": 27,
              "end": 36
            },
            {
              "footnote": "TG Disobedience.",
              "start": 46,
              "end": 57
            },
            {
              "footnote": "TG Lust.",
              "start": 84,
              "end": 89
            },
            {
              "footnote": "TG Malice.",
              "start": 115,
              "end": 121
            }
          ],
          "associatedContents": [],
          "italics": [
            {
              "start": 141,
              "end": 144
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "text": "But after that the kindness and love of God our Saviour toward man appeared,",
          "footnotes": [],
          "associatedContents": [],
          "italics": []
        },
        {
          "text": "Not by works of righteousness which we have done, but according to his mercy he saved us, by the washing of regeneration, and renewing of the Holy Ghost;",
          "footnotes": [
            {
              "footnote": "TG Righteousness.",
              "start": 16,
              "end": 29
            },
            {
              "footnote": "TG God, Mercy of.",
              "start": 71,
              "end": 76
            },
            {
              "footnote": "TG Baptism, Essential.",
              "start": 97,
              "end": 104
            },
            {
              "footnote": "TG Holy Ghost, Gifts of.",
              "start": 126,
              "end": 134
            }
          ],
          "associatedContents": [],
          "italics": []
        },
        {
          "text": "Which he shed on us abundantly through Jesus Christ our Saviour;",
          "footnotes": [],
          "associatedContents": [],
          "italics": []
        },
        {
          "text": "That being justified by his grace, we should be made heirs according to the hope of eternal life.",
          "footnotes": [
            {
              "footnote": "TG Justification.",
              "start": 11,
              "end": 20
            },
            {
              "footnote": "D&C 70:8.",
              "start": 53,
              "end": 58
            }
          ],
          "associatedContents": [],
          "italics": []
        },
        {
          "text": "This is a faithful saying, and these things I will that thou affirm constantly, that they which have believed in God might be careful to maintain good works. These things are good and profitable unto men.",
          "footnotes": [
            {
              "footnote": "TG Good Works.",
              "start": 151,
              "end": 156
            }
          ],
          "associatedContents": [],
          "italics": [
            {
              "start": 0,
              "end": 7
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "text": "But avoid foolish questions, and genealogies, and contentions, and strivings about the law; for they are unprofitable and vain.",
          "footnotes": [
            {
              "footnote": "2 Tim. 2:23 (23–26).",
              "start": 10,
              "end": 17
            },
            {
              "footnote": "TG Contention.",
              "start": 50,
              "end": 61
            }
          ],
          "associatedContents": [],
          "italics": []
        },
        {
          "text": "A man that is an heretick after the first and second admonition reject;",
          "footnotes": [
            {
              "footnote": "TG Apostasy of Individuals.",
              "start": 17,
              "end": 25
            },
            {
              "footnote": "Matt. 18:17.",
              "start": 53,
              "end": 63
            }
          ],
          "associatedContents": [],
          "italics": []
        },
        {
          "text": "Knowing that he that is such is subverted, and sinneth, being condemned of himself.",
          "footnotes": [
            {
              "footnote": "GR perverted, changed.",
              "start": 32,
              "end": 41
            }
          ],
          "associatedContents": [],
          "italics": []
        },
        {
          "text": "When I shall send Artemas unto thee, or Tychicus, be diligent to come unto me to Nicopolis: for I have determined there to winter.",
          "footnotes": [],
          "associatedContents": [],
          "italics": []
        },
        {
          "text": "Bring Zenas the lawyer and Apollos on their journey diligently, that nothing be wanting unto them.",
          "footnotes": [],
          "associatedContents": [],
          "italics": []
        },
        {
          "text": "And let ours also learn to maintain good works for necessary uses, that they be not unfruitful.",
          "footnotes": [
            {
              "footnote": "GR our people.",
              "start": 8,
              "end": 12
            },
            {
              "footnote": "Rom. 15:28 (25–28); Philip. 4:17.",
              "start": 36,
              "end": 46
            }
          ],
          "associatedContents": [],
          "italics": []
        },
        {
          "text": "All that are with me salute thee. Greet them that love us in the faith. Grace be with you all. Amen.",
          "footnotes": [],
          "associatedContents": [],
          "italics": [
            {
              "start": 78,
              "end": 80
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    }
  ]
}